Hoffmaster, Toshihisa Ishikawahttp://academic.research.microsoft.com/io.ashx?type=5&id=37039919&selfId1=-1&selfId2=-1&maxNumber=12&query=korean bbq san francisco review
Membrane transporters can be major determinants of the pharmacokinetic, safety and efficacy profiles of drugs. This presents several key questions for drug development, including which transporters are clinically important in drug absorption and disposition, and which in vitro methods are suitable for studying drug interactions with these transporters. In addition, what criteria should trigger follow-up clinical studies, and which ...
